HEADWORD: Timocracy
<hw>Ti*moc"ra*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/
honor, worth (fr. <?/ to honor) + <?/ to govern: cf. F.
<ets>timocratie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. Antiq.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A state in which the love of honor is the ruling motive.</def>
